Meet Our Team
BENN FELTHEIMER - MANAGING PARTNERBenn started  Feltheimer Cohn & Associates based on 30 years of money management and business development experience.Prior to forming Feltheimer Cohn & Associates in 2009, Mr. Feltheimer worked on a wealth management team at Merrill Lynch, Pierce, Fenner and Smith and began his investment career with First Investors Corporation, where as Senior Vice-President, he managed a sales force of over 1,100 advisors in 47 locations.   Chicago Magazine has recognized Mr. Feltheimer as a “Top 5 Star Wealth Manager in Chicago” in 2012, 2013, and 2014, reflecting a sustained high level of client trust and confidence*. His licenses include:  Series 6, 7, 63, 65, life insurance, and variable annuity.  He is designated as a Chartered Retirement Planning Counselor® by the College of Financial Planning.  Benn has been engaged in philanthropy throughout his career.  He currently serves as Vice Chair and member of the executive committee of Jewish Child and Family Services, a $40 million social services agency based in Chicago. AVRA COHN - MANAGING PARTNER                                       Avra joined Feltheimer Cohn & Associates, Inc. in 2009 with 30 years of money management experience, as well as 18 years in corporate management. Avra works with new client acquisition and specializes in individual and corporate retirement plans. She has been the featured speaker at client seminars as well as corporate conferences. Avra holds series 6, 7, 26, 63, 99 variable annuity and life insurance licenses and provides advisory services in AR, CA, FL, GA, IA, IL, IN, NJ, NY, PA, WA, and WI.Prior to joining Feltheimer Cohn & Associates, Inc.,  Avra worked as an Independent Registered Representative of Securities America, Inc. Previously, Avra served  as Vice President of  First Investors Corporation where she was responsible for opening several branch offices and supervising the training of over 100 managers and advisors.RICHARD WINER - CPA / REGISTERED REPRESENTATIVEFor years, Richard E. Winer, CPA, has been providing quality, personalized financial guidance to local individuals and businesses. His expertise ranges from basic tax management and accounting services to more in-depth services such as audits and financial statements.Mr. Winer owns one of the leading CPA firms on Chicago's North Shore and has worked with Benn Feltheimer and Avra Cohn for over 20 years. By combining his expertise, experience with a team mentality, he assures that every client receives the close analysis and attention they deserve. His dedicates himself to high standards in order to help clients maintain financial viability in the present, while taking a proactive approach to achieve future goals. This includes open communication to reach a better understanding of clients' needs through research and sound analysis. His dedication to hard work has earned the respect of the business and financial community in and around the Chicago area.TIMOTHY LUCOLE - OFFICE MANAGER / CLIENT ASSOCIATETim joined Feltheimer Cohn & Associates with 30 years of experience in supply chain management.  As an analyst and planner for Solo Cup and Quill Corporation, Tim was responsible for statistical forecasting, planning and distribution of merchandise across multiple product lines.Native to Chicago, he holds an undergraduate degree in business from Western Illinois University and an MBA from DeVry University.  Tim is licensed in life and long-term care insurance and has been active in local philanthropic social services throughout his career.   LADENBURG THALMANN FINANCIAL CORPORATIONSecurities America Advisors is a wholly owned subsidiary of Ladenburg Thalmann Financial Corporation. Ladenburg Thalmann  (AMEX: LTS) was established in 1876 and its businesses include Independent Brokerage & Advisory Services, Ladenburg Thalmann Asset Management Inc. and Ladenburg Thalmann & Co. Inc. for investment banking, equity research, institutional sales & trading and private client services. Please see www.ladenburg.com. 






share

|





 






Securities offered through Securities America, Inc.  Member FINRA/SIPC www.FINRA.org, www.SIPC.org.
Advisory services offered through Securities America Advisors, Inc., Benn Feltheimer and Avra Cohn Representatives.
Feltheimer Cohn and Associates is not affilliated with the Securities America companies.
Securities America and its representatives do not provide tax or legal advice.
Representatives are licensed to offer securities in AR, CA, FL, GA, IA, IL, IN, MD, NJ, NY, PA,
 WA and WI.  Representatives are licensed to offer insurance in IL, CO, FL, NJ, NY and VA.




